1- Install requirements.txt (This project is running on python 3.12.3) 
 run
`pip install -r requirements.txt`

2- Model spechs:
    'Eval_loss': 0.020717764273285866,
    'eval_accuracy': 0.98828125,
    'eval_f1': 0.9868629092261906,
    'eval_precision': 0.9977539062499999, 
    'eval_recall': 0.98828125,

# Training model with your own dataset
Tip: Use the fine_tune.py
(This Model is based of the BART model.)
Change from my default dataset "train.csv" to yours, on line 80.

# Starting the project 
`uvicorn main:app --reload`

# Requests
To get the query make a post request to /generate-query
 Example (using http for localhost):
  `http://127.0.0.1:8000/generate-query`

It is currently only accepting one parameter (question) in portuguese to be translate to english. This translations is skipped if it's already in english

# Example
  `    {
  "question": "Mostre me todos os livros de Jane Austen desde 1980"
}`
`
{
    "generated_sql": "SELECT Jane Austen books FROM table WHERE Year = 1980"
}
`